    <h1>Want To Work With Me ?</h1>
<div class="published">
  <span>Great news, keep reading!</span>
</div>

<div id="container">
  <div id="content">

    <div id="hire">
      <p>
        Currently I'm mostly focused on education and coaching,
        but I'm open to other kind of missions.
      </p>

      <h3>What I Can Do For You</h3>
      <p>
        Here's an incomplete list of the things I can help you with:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Teaching non technical people about development</strong></li>
        <li><strong>Coaching you or your team to create or scale a product</strong></li>
        <li><strong>Basic or advanced Ruby on Rails training</strong></li>
        <li>Implementing development best practices in your team</li>
        <li>One shot development projects</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Why I Can Help</h3>

      <p>
        I've been developing for quite a while now, and seen a lot of
        different environment, development methods and solved my share of
        problems. I also taught a lot of people, from entrepreneurs to
        designers, from developers to middle school students.
      </p>
      <p>
        Recently I helped a young team of entrepreneurs
        <a href="/blog/2014/12/16/coaching-startup-birdly-le-camping/">getting accepted</a>
        into a famous startup
        accelerator, taught students at HEC about
        <a href="http://theleanstartup.com/">Lean Startup</a>
        and gave a Ruby on Rails class at HETIC.
      </p>

